<div id="review_2954254966" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2954254966" />
    <a title="Whitney Atkinson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14457130-whitney-atkinson"><img alt="Whitney Atkinson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1550868411p2/14457130.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2954254966?book_show_action=true">Aug 27, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Whitney Atkinson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Whitney Atkinson" href="/user/show/14457130-whitney-atkinson">Whitney Atkinson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14457130-whitney-atkinson?shelf=read-in-2019">read-in-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14457130-whitney-atkinson?shelf=poetry">poetry</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14457130-whitney-atkinson?shelf=lgbtqiap">lgbtqiap</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2954254966" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1293674563715775755">It&apos;s getting more dificult for me to read poetry because I find a lot of it lingers in very &quot;middle of the road&quot; territory, which is how I felt this one was. Jericho&apos;s writing is certainly pretty and I highlighted a lot of impactful lines, but I also found myself skimming some poems that I couldn&apos;t quite comprehend, and there wasn&apos;t a poem in this collection that I loved start to finish, even though great messages and introspection are sprinkled throughout. I don&apos;t think this book is quite my ta</span>
  <span id="freeText1293674563715775755" style="display:none">It's getting more dificult for me to read poetry because I find a lot of it lingers in very "middle of the road" territory, which is how I felt this one was. Jericho's writing is certainly pretty and I highlighted a lot of impactful lines, but I also found myself skimming some poems that I couldn't quite comprehend, and there wasn't a poem in this collection that I loved start to finish, even though great messages and introspection are sprinkled throughout. I don't think this book is quite my taste in poetry, but it was still a nice collection about a black queer man that I enjoyed reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1293674563715775755" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


