        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3366161890" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8085104209586693472">The Tradition won the Pulitzer Prize for Poetry in 2020. So, I had high hopes for it. I, not being a fan of modern poetry, thought that this poetry collection could convince me otherwise, but I was wrong.<br/><br/>The poems discuss a lot of social and political topics like racism, rape, gun violence. There are some good bits in the poems. A couple of poems, I liked even, but I didn&apos;t like the form. It just didn&apos;t resonate with me.</span>
  <span id="freeText8085104209586693472" style="display:none">The Tradition won the Pulitzer Prize for Poetry in 2020. So, I had high hopes for it. I, not being a fan of modern poetry, thought that this poetry collection could convince me otherwise, but I was wrong.<br /><br />The poems discuss a lot of social and political topics like racism, rape, gun violence. There are some good bits in the poems. A couple of poems, I liked even, but I didn't like the form. It just didn't resonate with me.</span>
