<span id="freeTextContainer10964343868214834898">Many of the poems in the first half of this book focus on the political. Most in the second dwell on the personal. You might like one or the other or both. <br/><br/>For a sample poem, along with one from a book I read at the same time, <i>American Sonnets for My Past and Future Assassin</i>, you can <a href='https://kencraftpoetry.wordpress.com/2019/08/05/twin-poetry-peaks-terrance-hayes-and-jericho-brown/' rel='nofollow noopener'>go down this rabbit hole.</a>.</span>
