    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3043832714" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3043832714" />
    <a title="Debbie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22443749-debbie"><img alt="Debbie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546379381p2/22443749.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3043832714?book_show_action=true">Aug 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Debbie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Debbie" href="/user/show/22443749-debbie">Debbie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/52136448-the-tradition">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22443749-debbie?shelf=poetry">poetry</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3043832714" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9705589753813772760">3.5 stars<br/><br/>I’m definitely one of the very few who feel this way, but the style many of these poems just wasn’t for me.<br/><br/>You could viscerally feel how personal and meaningful these poems were to the author, which I appreciate, respect and admire. But the rhythm, cadence and flow of many of them weren’t quite there for me personally.<br/><br/>I do truly believe this is a case of “it’s not you, it’s me.” Jericho Brown is obviously an immensely talented poet, as portrayed by the clever wordplay and poetic explora</span>
  <span id="freeText9705589753813772760" style="display:none">3.5 stars<br /><br />I’m definitely one of the very few who feel this way, but the style many of these poems just wasn’t for me.<br /><br />You could viscerally feel how personal and meaningful these poems were to the author, which I appreciate, respect and admire. But the rhythm, cadence and flow of many of them weren’t quite there for me personally.<br /><br />I do truly believe this is a case of “it’s not you, it’s me.” Jericho Brown is obviously an immensely talented poet, as portrayed by the clever wordplay and poetic explorations present in many of the poems, as well as his ability to draw emotions from his poetry. They just didn’t quite stick with me personally.<br /><br />(And 3.5 stars isn’t a bad rating by any means, just not quite at the level of the 4 to 5 star ratings that abound for this collection).</span>
  <a data-text-id="9705589753813772760" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


