<div id="review_3321729154" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3321729154" />
    <a title="Theodore" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/76389089-theodore"><img alt="Theodore" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1556935966p2/76389089.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3321729154?book_show_action=true">May 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Theodore" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Theodore" href="/user/show/76389089-theodore">Theodore</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/76389089-theodore?shelf=black-authors">black-authors</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/76389089-theodore?shelf=poetry">poetry</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/76389089-theodore?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/76389089-theodore?shelf=lgbtq">lgbtq</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3321729154" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2494068382574903006">i don&apos;t have the range to judge, rate or critique poetry. my level of understanding of this art form is minimal at best. with that said, i&apos;ve taken the time to slowly introduce myself to it because i love prose - the evocation though language and words which is why folks love poetry so much. <br/><br/>The Tradition by Jericho Brown was beautifully layered, addressing traditions in love, sexuality, gender, and racism. Brown well deserves the award for this powerful book.</span>
  <span id="freeText2494068382574903006" style="display:none">i don't have the range to judge, rate or critique poetry. my level of understanding of this art form is minimal at best. with that said, i've taken the time to slowly introduce myself to it because i love prose - the evocation though language and words which is why folks love poetry so much. <br /><br />The Tradition by Jericho Brown was beautifully layered, addressing traditions in love, sexuality, gender, and racism. Brown well deserves the award for this powerful book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2494068382574903006" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
